data.title: Kansas State University
data.text:
2016: Did not see any game action.

COMMUNITY COLLEGE: Played in six games at Coffeyville Community College in 2013 under head coach Aaron Flores, helping the Ravens earn a 4-5 record… Participated in spring practices at Hutchinson CC in 2014 under Rion Rhodes.

HIGH SCHOOL: Played four seasons at Louisburg under head coach Garry Griffin... Helped lead the Wildcats to a combined 34-12 record over his four seasons, including a perfect 14-0 sophomore campaign in 2010 that culminated with a state championship… Earned second team all-state honors as a defensive tackle.

PERSONAL: Konnor Lee Cook was born October 7, 1994, in Louisburg, Kansas… Son of James and Anita Cook… Father, Jim, attended K-State… Older brother, Kody, played wide receiver and quarterback for the Wildcats in 2014 and 2015… Majoring in social sciences.
